'''Banjari''' is one of the popular [[Hindu deity]] in [[Odisha, India|Odisha]], India.  There are many Banjari temples present in the western and southern parts of Odisha. [[File:Maa Banjari Mandir-Nials.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Modern Banjari Temple in [[Majursahi]]]] The Banjari temple in [[Majursahi]] is well-recognized in Odisha. Banjari is also the primary deity associated with the Nial family of Majursahi in [[Majursahi Nial Family|Majursahi]]. Magha Puja is one of the most popular festivals of Banjari at Majursahi. Chaitra is a festival associated with Banjari in Majursahi.

