}}{{Short description|Hindu deity}}
'''Varchas''' ({{Lang-sa|वर्चस्|translit=Varcas}}) is a [[Hindu deities|Hindu deity]]. He is one of the eight [[Vasu|Vasus]]. He is the son of [[Chandra]], the moon god, and [[Rohini (goddess)|Rohini]], a daughter of [[Daksha]] and the chief consort of Chandra.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Hall|first=Fitzedward|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=f-ooAAAAYAAJ&q=%22Varchas%22+-wikipedia&pg=PA228|title=The Vishńu Puráńa: A System of Hindu Mythology and Tradition|date=1877|publisher=Trübner|language=en}}</ref> According to the [[Mahabharata]], [[Arjuna|Arjuna's]] and [[Subhadra|Subhadra's]] son, [[Abhimanyu]], is regarded to be his incarnation.<ref>{{Cite book |last=Anonymous |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ygA2240G74kC&dq=Varchas+Soma&pg=PT382 |title=The Mahabharata of Krishna-Dwaipayana Vyasa (Complete) |publisher=Library of Alexandria |isbn=978-1-4655-2637-3 |pages=382 |language=en}}</ref>

== Legend ==
According to the Mahabharata, a conference once took place among the [[Deva (Hinduism)|devas]] and Chandra, where it was proposed that Varchas be incarnated on earth for the destruction of wicked men. Chandra did not wish to be separated from his beloved son, but consented to the proposition, on the condition that Varchas would not leave him for more than sixteen years. Accordingly, during the [[Dvapara Yuga]], Varchas was born as [[Abhimanyu]], the son of the [[Pandava]] prince, [[Arjuna]], and the [[Yadu dynasty|Yadava]] princess, [[Subhadra]]. Abhimanyu was slain when he was sixteen fighting in the [[Kurukshetra War]].<ref>{{Cite book |last=Mani |first=Vettam |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mvXsDwAAQBAJ&dq=Varcas+Abhimanyu&pg=PR1 |title=Puranic Encyclopedia: A Comprehensive Work with Special Reference to the Epic and Puranic Literature |date=2015-01-01 |publisher=Motilal Banarsidass |isbn=978-81-208-0597-2 |pages=1 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |last=Garg |first=Gaṅgā Rām |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=w9pmo51lRnYC&dq=Varcas+Abhimanyu&pg=PA107 |title=Encyclopaedia of the Hindu World |date=1992 |publisher=Concept Publishing Company |isbn=978-81-7022-374-0 |pages=107 |language=en}}</ref>

