{{Short description|Epithet of Shiva}} [[File:Myths of the Hindus & Buddhists - Shiva drinking the World-Poison.jpg|thumb|Shiva drinks the kalakuta, rendering his throat blue.]] '''Nilakanta''' ({{Lang-sa|नीलकण्ठ|lit=blue throat|translit=Nīlakaṇṭha}}) is one of the epithets of the [[Hinduism|Hindu]] deity [[Shiva]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=www.wisdomlib.org |date=2015-12-01 |title=Nilakantha, Nīlakaṇṭha, Nila-kantha, Nilakamtha: 28 definitions |url=https://www.wisdomlib.org/definition/nilakantha |access-date=2022-11-06 |website=www.wisdomlib.org |language=en}}</ref>
==Legend== {{See also|Samudra Manthana}} According to [[Hindu mythology]], [[Shiva]] gained this epithet when he consumed the [[Halahala|kalakuta]] (poison) that emerged from [[Samudra manthan|Samudra Manthana]], which rendered his throat blue.<ref>{{Cite web |last=www.wisdomlib.org |date=2017-01-29 |title=Halahala, Halāhala, Hālāhala, Halahalā, Hālahala: 22 definitions |url=https://www.wisdomlib.org/definition/halahala |access-date=2022-11-06 |website=www.wisdomlib.org |language=en}}</ref>
